    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_1982730474" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1982730474" />
    <a title="Matthew" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/16254355-matthew"><img alt="Matthew" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1464987365p2/16254355.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1982730474?book_show_action=true">Jan 10, 2021</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Matthew" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Matthew" href="/user/show/16254355-matthew">Matthew</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Audiobook 9780739382868" href="/book/show/13135114-cutting-for-stone">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/16254355-matthew?shelf=audio">audio</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/16254355-matthew?shelf=historical-fiction">historical-fiction</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/16254355-matthew?shelf=2021">2021</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1982730474" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer4813203937907097426">Great storytelling! I was captivated throughout.<br/><br/>The first time I heard about this book my brother-in-law and all of his medical school friends were reading it and couldn&apos;t say enough about how amazing it was. After reading it and seeing how much of it has to do with medicine and surgery, it makes perfect sense.<br/><br/>I really enjoyed getting to know all the characters and, seeing them deal with the social constructs of mid-20th century Ethiopia. Also, the author pulls no punches when it comes to the he</span>
  <span id="freeText4813203937907097426" style="display:none">Great storytelling! I was captivated throughout.<br /><br />The first time I heard about this book my brother-in-law and all of his medical school friends were reading it and couldn't say enough about how amazing it was. After reading it and seeing how much of it has to do with medicine and surgery, it makes perfect sense.<br /><br />I really enjoyed getting to know all the characters and, seeing them deal with the social constructs of mid-20th century Ethiopia. Also, the author pulls no punches when it comes to the heart-wrenching twists and turns they all go through. Very amazing job done by Verghese.<br /><br />I mention that there is a lot of medical content here. I recently read The Pull of the Stars by Emma Donoghue and I am reminded a lot of that book. What it comes down to is the medical content makes up a large portion of the book and most of it is very graphic - the author does not lighten things up. I think it is good that the harsh realities are shared and it is very important to the story. But, if you are easily queasy or can only stand a little intense medical content here and there, proceed with caution or do not proceed at all.<br /><br />I have something about this book that I have to get off my chest. It does not detract from my rating and it is not a criticism of the overall quality of the book. I am marking it with a spoiler because I think it gives too much away. <a class="jsShowSpoiler spoilerAction">(view spoiler)</a><span class="spoilerContainer" style="display: none">[The last 1/4 of the book or so PISSED ME OFF! Everything from the time Genet finds Marion in America through the end of the book was infuriating. And, just when you think it cannot get worse, it does! I loved the book, but if I had been reading a physical copy, there are several times I would have flung the book across the room. Marion just keeps getting the rawest of deals! And, Genet - whoo, boy! I think you are supposed to feel sorry for her, but I was too busy being ticked off at her! <a class="jsHideSpoiler spoilerAction">(hide spoiler)</a>]</span><br /><br />Summary: A great book - be prepared for frustration and some stomach churning medical content</span>
  <a data-text-id="4813203937907097426" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


